      "children": [],
      "content_layer": "body",
      "label": "paragraph",
      "prov": [],
      "orig": "Yes, I know that a /64 IPv6 network contains 18,446,744,073,709,551,616 addresses and that should be enough for most home networks. Using one /64 network block per interface has plenty of benefits for simplifying your network, though.",
