      "orig": "Every ISP is a bit different with how they assign IPv6 addresses and what size blocks they will allocate to you. I've seen where some will only give a /64, others give a /56, and others give something in between. As for Spectrum, they provide up to a /56 with a prefix delegation request. You may need to experiment with a /56 first and slowly back down towards /64 to see what your ISP might do.",
      "text": "Every ISP is a bit different with how they assign IPv6 addresses and what size blocks they will allocate to you. I've seen where some will only give a /64, others give a /56, and others give something in between. As for Spectrum, they provide up to a /56 with a prefix delegation request. You may need to experiment with a /56 first and slowly back down towards /64 to see what your ISP might do."
